orbitSensitivity.title: Orbit Sensitivity
orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster

orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster

distanceMax.title: Distance Max
distanceMax.description: Setting this at 0 will give an infinite distance limit

inertiaFactor.title: Inertia Factor
inertiaFactor.description: Higher value means that the camera will continue moving after the user has stopped dragging. 0 is fully responsive.

focusEntity.title: Focus Entity
focusEntity.description: Entity for the camera to focus on. If blank, then the camera will use the whole scene

frameOnStart.title: Frame on Start
frameOnStart.description: Frames the entity or scene at the start of the application."

precision.description: Number of decimal digits rendered in text.

dofMaxBlur.title: Max Blur
dofMaxBlur.description: The amount of blurring that will occur.

dofAperture.title: Aperture
dofAperture.description: Defines the opening on the rear of the 'lens' that determines the amount of light that is allowed to travel through.

dofFocus.title: Focus
dofFocus.description: The distance from the camera of the focus point where the effect is centered on.

dofRange.title: Range
dofRange.description: The area around the focus point where blurring is gradually applied on.

dofAspect.title: Aspect
dofAspect.description: Determines the base of the 'lens' starting point.

dofDebug.title: Debug
dofDebug.description: Ideal to find the correct focus point, white areas get blurred.

godLightPosition.title: Light Emitter
godLightPosition.description: Drag and drop any entity (not necessarily a light), its world position will be used to calculate the center of the effect on screen.

godQuality.title: Quality
godQuality.description: Three presets for quality are available from Low to High, better quality with the cost in performance. This property requires reloading the effect to render the new value.

godIntensity.title: Intensity
godIntensity.description: The intensity of the light accumulated in the center of the effect.

godWeight.title: Weight
godWeight.description: Determines the outer rim of the light on the center of the effect.

godDecay.title: Decay
godDecay.description: Determines how fast the rays will decay from the light source.

godExposure.title: Exposure
godExposure.description: A multiplier to increase exponentially the amount of light calculated.

godColor.title: Color
godColor.description: The color of the light source.

saoFar.title: Far
saoFar.description: A ratio of how fast from the camera the effect fades out, larger values render the effect in greater view distances but in lower quality due to smaller precision.

saoSamples.title: Samples
saoSamples.description: The number of samples collected per pixel to calculate the total occlusion. Larger values provide better quality but can have a performance hit. This property requires reloading the effect to render the new value.

saoIntensity.title: Intensity
saoIntensity.description: Determines how dark the calculated occlusion is rendered.

saoScale.title: Scale
saoScale.description: Determines how far from the world position of the pixel occlusion sample points will be collected.

saoBias.title: Bias
saoBias.description: A ratio that discards any sample point that falls in that range used to decrease artifacts on edges. The value should be visually estimated depending on the rendered models.

saoKernelRadius.title: Kernel Radius
saoKernelRadius.description: Determines the radius of the occlusion effect around a pixel.

saoBlurRadius.title: Blur Radius
saoBlurRadius.description: Blurs within the given radius the collected occlusion points to render a final smooth shadow.

saoDebug.title: Debug
saoDebug.description: Ideal to check how the effect is rendered and adjust the parameters.

filmicVignette.title: Vignette
filmicVignette.description: If checked vignette will be enabled. This property requires reloading the effect to render the new value.

filmicVignetteOffset.title: Vignette Offset
filmicVignetteOffset.description: The offset from the corner that vignette will have.

filmicVignetteColor.title: Color
filmicVignetteColor.description: The color of the vignette effect.

filmicAberration.title: Chromatic Aberration
filmicAberration.description: If checked chromatic aberration will be enabled. This property requires reloading the effect to render the new value.

filmicAberrationAmount.title: Chr. Aberration Amount
filmicAberrationAmount.description: The amount of chromatic aberration applied.

filmicAberrationAnimated.title: Chr. Aberration Animated
filmicAberrationAnimated.description: If checked the chromatic aberration will be animated using a shaking tween. This property requires reloading the effect to render the new value.

filmicSharpen.title: Sharpen
filmicSharpen.description: If checked sharpen will be enabled. It can't be used together with Pixelate. This property requires reloading the effect to render the new value.

filmicGrain.title: Film Grain
filmicGrain.description: If checked film grain and noise will be added. This property requires reloading the effect to render the new value.

filmicGrainAmount.title: Grain Amount
filmicGrainAmount.description: The amount of film grain applied.

filmicPixelate.title: Pixelate
filmicPixelate.description: If checked pixelate will be enabled. It can't be used together with Sharpen. This property requires reloading the effect to render the new value.

filmicGrayscale.title: Grayscale
filmicGrayscale.description: If checked the final image will be converted to grayscale. This property requires reloading the effect to render the new value.

motionBlurSamples.title: Samples
motionBlurSamples.description: The number of samples collected per pixel to calculate the total motion blur. Larger values provide better quality but can have a performance hit. This property requires reloading the effect to render the new value.

motionBlurStrength.title: Strength
motionBlurStrength.description: Determines how intense the calculated motion blurring is.

adaptionMinLuminance.title: Min Luminance
adaptionMinLuminance.description: Determines the minimum luminance difference between light/dark regions to affect the target exposure.

adaptionTau.title: Adaption Offset
adaptionTau.description: The maximum offset (plus/minus) to be added to the base scene exposure.

EffectDof.title: DOF
EffectDof.description: Check to enable Depth of Field (DOF).

EffectSAO.title: SAO
EffectSAO.description: Check to enable Scalable Ambient Occlusion (SAO). If you experience artifacts/banding on vertical edges increase the your camera rear clipping plane to a higher value e.g. 0.1 or 1.0

EffectFilmic.title: Filmic
EffectFilmic.description: A number of effects that simulate the function of a camera lens.

EffectMotionBlur.title: Motion Blur
EffectMotionBlur.description: Check to enable a camera based motion blur effect.

EffectAdaptiveEye.title: Adaptive Eye
EffectAdaptiveEye.description: Check to enable an adaptive eye exposure effect.

camera.title: Camera
camera.description: Set the active camera to render the post effects to. If none is provided the script will attempt to find a camera named 'Camera'.

mobilePerformance.title: Mobile Performance
mobilePerformance.description: If selected, effects not working on mobile devices will be turned off automatically when running on a non supported device.

mobileAutoDisable.title: Mobile Disable
mobileAutoDisable.description: If selected all effects will be turned off automatically when running on a mobile/tablet device.
